  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.contemporist.com/this-wood-watchtower-is-also-a-home-for-bats/\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-tower-171024-700-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Koen Mol\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.nextarchitects.com/\"\u003eNEXT Architects\u003c/a\u003e has shared photos of Watchtower Einderheide, a lookout in The Netherlands, that also doubles as a shelter for bats.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1500\" height=\"2007\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01.jpg 1500w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01-940x1258.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01-800x1070.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01-768x1028.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-01-1148x1536.jpg 1148w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Koen Mol\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt a height of 85 feet (26m), there’s a view of the Brabantse Kempen’s wooded area surrounding it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1500\" height=\"2008\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02.jpg 1500w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02-940x1258.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02-800x1071.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02-768x1028.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-architecture-171024-704-02-1147x1536.jpg 1147w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Koen Mol\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNotches, at different heights and on different sides of the design, provide a view during the climb to the top. The facade consists of laminated larch columns covered with thermally preserved pine.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1875\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01.jpg 1500w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01-940x1175.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-01-1229x1536.jpg 1229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-02.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-02.jpg 1500w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-02-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-02-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-02-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1500\" height=\"2251\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03.jpg 1500w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03-940x1411.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03-800x1201.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03-768x1153.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-architecture-171024-709-03-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eA spiral staircase leads up to the viewing platform, with two other floors located on the way for people that don’t want to go to the top.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-01-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-02-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe tower is not only intended for the view but also, through the use of wood, provides shelter for tree-dwelling bats. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1707\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03.jpg 1707w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03-940x1410.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-03-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eA diversity of niches and cavities have been created at several heights in the structure with different types of habitats, such as winter and summer quarters and mating and nesting sites.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1281\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-04-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese hives were specially developed for this project by ecologist Jeroen Mos. The wood not only fits well into the wooded environment, but it also contributes to imitating the natural habitat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1281\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-05-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe roughness of the wood used to build the watchtower gives the bats grip so they can land and crawl away.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1281\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-06-1536x1025.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/watchtower-lookout-171024-711-07-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Karl Banski\u003c/h6\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHere’s a drawing from the architects that shows the design process.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"391\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01.jpg\" alt=\"A modern wood watchtower which acts as a lookout and as a bat habitat.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01-940x191.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01-800x163.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01-768x156.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/architectural-drawing-watchtower-171024-716-01-1536x313.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003eDesign: NEXT Architects | Design Team: Michel Schreinemachers, Bart Reuser, Marijn Schenk with Bobby de Graaf, Douwe Strating, Angelos Chouliaris, Sonia Cunha, Vyasa Koe, Monika Popkiewicz | Collaborators: H+N+S Landschapsarchitects, Boskalis, WSP, Mos Ecologisch Advies en Onderzoek, Gemeente Bergeijk, KunstLoc Brabant, Elianne van Elderen (schrijver/dichter), Houthandel Van Dal (leverancier en hoofdaannemer), Reijrink Staalconstructie, Van De Sande (fundering)\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
